      "definition": "Envelope structure where the same phrase or image opens and closes a unit, delimiting it.",
      "examples": [
        "Ecclesiastes (vanity of vanities at 1:2 and 12:8)",
        "Psalm 8 (How majestic is your name at v.1 and v.9)",
        "Psalm 103 (Bless the LORD, O my soul)",
        "Genesis 1-9 (be fruitful and multiply)",
        "Johannine prologue (the Word at John 1:1 and 1:18)"
      ],
      "suggested_edges": [
        {"kind": "brackets", "from": "inclusio", "to": "pericope"},
